reviews.title: What a top tent
reviews.text: What a great place this is. Fantastic dishes. Fantastic service. And a beautiful location. Completely finished. Highly recommended.

reviews.title: Recommended!
reviews.text: Great food and enjoyed the good wine! Friendly staff, good quality food and nice location. In short, highly recommended!

reviews.title: A deserved anniversary
reviews.text:
Twelve and a half years of high-level cooking has been going on here. 
We have experienced this many times here. 
This anniversary menu was perfect again, a strong kitchen team
brings beautiful flavorful amuses and dishes to the table. The service is competent, friendly and creates a relaxed atmosphere. 
For all the work and quality, the prices are very fair.
We highly recommend this restaurant!

reviews.title: Delightful and beautiful
reviews.text: For us the 2nd time we went here because of our wedding day and again it was delicious! You also get nice amuses. The dishes look beautiful. The service is good, so really highly recommended.

reviews.title: Delicious lunch.
reviews.text: At circular walk Harlingen we wanted to have lunch. Cheese sandwich or something. We walked in at the Havenmanche and it turned into one big party. Delicious lunch, not a cheese sandwich, but culinary super. Nice service. One big party! Enjoyed it. (And even the price wasn't so bad...)

reviews.title: Perfect
reviews.text: What a lovely, cozy evening; food perfect, service perfect, seating perfect, wine perfect;-) This was the second time since we moved to Harlingen in our old age and definitely a challenge for next time, what a total picture! So see you soon.

reviews.title: Guaranteed quality
reviews.text:
Marco Poldervaart has an excellent kitchen team that also delivers the quality during his absence, which we have experienced several times.
The dishes are all very tasty and made up with attention to detail. The Havenmanche is also known for its amuses. It is not a small spoon here but a nicely balanced small dish. 
The service is also friendly and knowledgeable. You feel welcome and spoiled here.

reviews.title: Great food with a star!
reviews.text:
Great food at good price and good service. The 3-course menu with all the amuses was certainly sufficient!
One spot at the window is recommended because of the view.

reviews.title: Unique place
reviews.text:
Everything good

We had lunch at this restaurant today and the experience was fantastic. Our hostes was knowledgeable, pleasant and friendly. The food was spot on. We went for a 3 course lunch and it reminded us that cooking is an art. Well done to the staff and thanks for making this a very pleasant experience!

reviews.title: Good food on the harbor.
reviews.text: Very nicely located on the harbor of Harlingen. Nice atmosphere and cozy decor. The food was high in taste. The service was very slow. Keep in mind that you sit for a long time, if that is not a problem, the Havenmantjse is an absolute must.

reviews.title: Very good and welcoming
reviews.text: Lunch package booked and this was a beautiful experience. Waitstaff not only know how to do it, but do everything they can to make it a pleasant experience. Compliments! Dishes were surprising and from amuse to dessert original and tasteful. And then the price is not so bad. In short: a top restaurant and that in a beautiful place. Highly recommended!

reviews.title: Recommended
reviews.text: Great location in Harlingen, with nice view of the harbour and good terrace. Food is fabulous! Service is really too slow.

reviews.title: Just a nice dinner
reviews.text: We enjoyed the 4 course dinner. All the different flavors of both the amuse-bouche and all the courses were a real surprise. The service was friendly and correct.

reviews.title: Couldn't be better.
reviews.text:
It has been a few days since we had dinner at Havenmantsje on Liberation Day and I now look back on our visit with great pleasure. Everything went perfectly that afternoon.

It started with a cocktail on the front terrace in the late afternoon sun, where we were served our first appetizers. Then we went inside for a delicious 6-course dinner, which took the entire evening.

We already knew that Marco and his chefs can cook, because we had previously taken a cooking course with Marco. We also came to this restaurant before, but it was never as good as this time. We always give points to the dishes and except for a 7 for one appetizer, all other ratings were consistently between 8 and 10! In addition, delicious wines were served with the wine arrangement, which completed the evening.
The service was not very experienced, but being helped by a friendly, service-oriented and charming working student makes up for a lot.
In short, a fantastic experience.

reviews.title: A more than outstanding restaurant really highly recommended
reviews.text:
This was our second time in the restaurant.
This time we had the 5-course menu with wine pairing.
It was once again a more than outstanding evening with excellent and superbly prepared food.
The wine pairing was really well matched to the dishes.
The staff is unique and very, very helpful. Every dish and every wine is explained very well.
It was once again outstanding and we will definitely come back.
A big thank you to the whole team for this great evening

questions.content: Hoi, zijn honden welkom in jullie restaurant? Alvast bedankt voor de reactie. Groetjes

Hallo, wir haben einen mittelgroßen Hund, ist dieser erlaubt?
Vielen Dank
Zijn jullie vandaag open ? Wij willen graag lunchen

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

articleContent.title: 10 things Paris is known for (with local-approved experiences)

seoInfo.metaDescription: From hidden gardens to iconic landmarks, explore the City of Light beyond the tourist traps.

articleContent.title: How many days in Dubai is enough?

seoInfo.metaDescription: Here’s how to make the most of the UAE’s most iconic city, whether you’ve got one day or a full week.

articleContent.title: A little person's guide to accessible Maui

seoInfo.metaDescription: Snorkel trips, beach days, and plenty of stand-out meals.

randomContentList.sponsorDisplayName: Fort Myers – Islands, Beaches and Neighborhoods

tripContent.title: Head to Fort Myers for amazing outdoor adventures
tripContent.description: Seeking adventure on your next vacation? Head to the greater Fort Myers area, where action-packed onshore and offshore activities are yours to enjoy year-round. Water sports, nature parks and wildlife excursions are just some of the highlights on this itinerary that is all about having fun in the sun.

tripContent.title: Chase horizons and conquer trails across Nevada’s rugged backcountry
tripContent.description: Nevada’s wild places were made for those who move at their own pace. Wander through desert canyons, alpine lakes, and ancient rock formations, all in one trip. Whether you're chasing stars in a dark sky park or breathing deep in the high mountains, this is the untamed side of the Silver State, ready to be roamed, hiked, and discovered.

articleContent.title: Having blind faith on the slopes

seoInfo.metaDescription: Visually impaired alpine ski racer Danelle Umstead has learned to channel fear into adrenaline, trusting her husband and guide, Rob Umstead, to lead her down the slopes with his voice.

tripContent.title: The Wanderer's guide to Saudi Arabia
tripContent.description: "When Laviai, Marsha, and I set out for Saudi Arabia with "The Wanderer" we had no idea how much this journey would change us. We expected stunning landscapes, rich history, and great food—but what we didn’t expect was how deeply we’d connect with the country and its people. From the moment we arrived, we were met with kindness and curiosity, and when we left, it felt as if we were saying goodbye to a home we'd only just discovered. This guide is our way of sharing our firsthand experiences. Whether you're planning your first visit or just curious about what makes Saudi Arabia so special, we hope our perspectives help you see this country with wide eyes, open hearts, and an endless sense of wonder." – Lina

seoInfo.metaDescription: This two-day São Paulo itinerary is a playbook for first-time and repeat visitors alike.

reviews.title: Not fulfilled.
reviews.text: It took a while before we received attention and were given the menu. In the end it took 80 minutes before the first of the ordered four fixed menu courses was served. When we asked what caused the slow pace of events, we were told that it had taken us a long time to have amuses. Whose deed. When we asked earlier for some bread, we were told that this would be part of the first course. Here again the explicit reference to the card with 'bites'. A way to generate extra turnover to cover up the long wait - or is the customer sent to the bites to satisfy their appetite? Neither our wine nor our water was replenished, before coffee we were asked if we were interested in friandis, our denial meant three cups of coffee in the barest possible way. After 260 minutes at the table, we left disappointed at this restaurant that did not live up to its Michelin star at all, while the kitchen certainly has potential. The nice location on the harbor and the flow of tourists have apparently made people lazy and self-righteous here, which is a shame.

reviews.title: Wine!
reviews.text: Nice location at the beginning of the harbour. Attractively decorated, hospitable service and nice bites with drinks. Highly recommended!

reviews.title: Delicious dinner
reviews.text:
Super fun evening with true works of art and delicious dishes. Perfect wines and nice service.
Our group sat in a nice corner with a good view and yet somewhat separated from the other guests.

reviews.title: This is the place for an evening of art on your plate and casual dining.
reviews.text:
What a nice evening we had.
Enjoyed from arrival to departure.
We sat on the left side downstairs, a very homely space, warmly decorated, very nice atmosphere.

From the appetizer to the last course, we enjoyed it very relaxed and casual.
The staff at the table are knowledgeable and pleasant in explaining dishes and matching wines.

We don't go often, so it remains a treat to pop in here every now and then, but absolutely worth it.

reviews.title: Yes, it remains very tasty
reviews.text: Here's another get via Groupon, but what a wonderful evening. Quickly come back here to roe. Service was good. Company doctor outing had a nice time, it's a pity that some guests don't appreciate that. See you soon

reviews.title: Excellent food and a very nice atmosphere
reviews.text: Excellent reception, service was hospitable and friendly. The restaurant is beautifully decorated with beautiful lighting and has a cozy atmosphere. And then we come to the food. Wow, what a real party that was; works of art on the plates and such delicious flavors. The wines paired well with the dishes and tasted excellent. We will definitely come back!

reviews.title: Last dinner of our holiday in the North
reviews.text: What to say; very good in all aspects, the welcome, seating, the choice, the amuse, the food, the service etc etc. If i may mention one tiny negative point, the tables were rather tightly placed and with my poor hearing i had difficulties hearing my wife but all tables were fully booked, a tribute to the excellence of the place. Chapeau...

reviews.title: Fantastic food and excellent service
reviews.text:
We had a wonderful lunch here this week. The all included 3 course lunch was excellent and the wine pairings superb. 
Service was very good and friendly. 
Our lunch was a fantastic start to a memorable stay in Harlingen. 
I would recommend!

reviews.title: Yes for lunch!
reviews.text: Try the marinated oysters!  Beautiful presentations in a beautiful setting. There oysters were fabulous . What an interesting village

reviews.title: Delicious food and enjoyment
reviews.text: Enjoyed a delicious 5-course dinner with wine pairing. We were surprised by the chef and it was not disappointing. Every course was a party.

reviews.title: Delicious, special, enjoy
reviews.text: What a special experience it is every time. Excellent service that completed the beautiful evening. Wonderful experience. Enjoyed with capital letters.

reviews.title: Surprisingly brilliant
reviews.text: I came here for a work event. Having never really ventured much beyond Amsterdam I was really surprised to find such a great restaurant in a port in the north of the Netherlands. Beautifully crafted food, friendly and knowledgeable staff (great wine pairings) and really nice environment. Bravo!

reviews.title: Completely different from an average restaurant. Special dishes. Beautifully served. Explanation of what is on your plate. At sometime
reviews.text: Two course lunch with appetizer. Top. A taste festival. Special dishes. You have to let yourself be surprised.

reviews.title: Great experience
reviews.text: Delicious food. Service is good but a bit stiff. They tell you exactly what's on your plate, but it's a bit slow. But you definitely eat there.

reviews.title: a world-class affair at the port of Harlingen
reviews.text:
advice from a former restaurant owner in Haringen who should know. a fantastic tip!
We have rarely eaten so well and also had various amuses beforehand, a world-class affair worthy of a star, we will definitely come back, it is a pity that we live in the Gooi (a good hour's drive) otherwise they would see us there every week.
Ted Kool

reviews.title: Now a tradition, it does not disappoint
reviews.text:
Vlieland, a lovely island but not a top culinary destination. So we traditionally take a hotel or B&B in Harlingen the evening before the crossing and treat ourselves to dinner at Het Havenmantsje.
And this year the menu with 4 courses and appetizers will not disappoint.
Delicious food, nice bottle of wine.
The only downside: the acoustics upstairs are not great, so the staff is used to talking very loudly.

reviews.title: How delicious it was again!
reviews.text:
To start our holiday, we booked again at 't Havermantsje for a 5-course surprise menu.
It was delicious again. Service top, atmosphere cozy food a 10!
So highly recommended!

reviews.title: Enjoy delicious dishes.
reviews.text: Another delicious meal! You really enjoy it when you are there. This time we sat in the conservatory and looked out over the harbour. Our menu consisted of various courses and each time it was a real surprise!

reviews.title: You must have been here!
reviews.text: Had my birthday dinner with my love. We enjoyed it so much. What really sets this restaurant apart is the quality of the service. The staff were attentive and professional, always willing and eager to ensure my dining experience was perfect. They had an excellent knowledge of the wine to match the meals. All in all, I highly recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a culinary experience. It combines excellent food, a friendly atmosphere and attentive service, making it an absolute must visit. I'll definitely return!

reviews.title: Wonderful place, good spirit, excellent food and service
reviews.text: We have been there on a wonderful summer evening. Service is Personal very friendly and atentive. Even as the place was packen, they always had an eye on us. Food is outstanding,  for me as a foodie such an expression means something.  A wide range from oysters to bavette via halibut and Desserts, ..... also the wine was very good. All in all the best experience for me of 2023.

reviews.title: Wonderful Food
reviews.text: We happened upon this as we walked along the harbour.  It was very inviting and when we sat for drinks we decided to have their 3 course meal.  Wow beautifully presented, lovely flavours and good size plates - we were satisfied but not bursting.  Definitely would go again.

reviews.title: Sensory wonderland in a hidden part of Holland
reviews.text: Who could have imagined the sensory flavours at Restaurant ‘t Havenmantsje. By far the best restaurant in central Harlingen, superlative attention to detail, world class communication of ingredients. A sensory wonderland that pushed flavours in new directions. Avocado in the dessert: but wow, who would have known it could tickle the palate in such a way.

reviews.title: Top location
reviews.text: We had the 5 course surprise dinner and were in for a real treat. The veal in blanc beurre sauce was great. The salmon with lardon was very good. The slow cooked pig knuckle was unbelievable. We ended our meal with a fine piece of ox with space hollandaise. The wine pairing was a great choice. My partner had a tea arrangement; the tea selected by the staff for each course was a good match. The service was very attentive and the atmosphere very relaxed. Bottomline: everything works in this restaurant and we had one of the best meals during our trip in Friesland.

reviews.title: Delicious ‘surprise’ dinner
reviews.text: A delicious dinner here in a sunny Friday night. The food was beautifully presented and all was a great variety of fresh, interesting local flavours with international influences. The Marbre Duck starter was a highlight. The outside tables, next to the bustling harbour in a beautiful warm evening, were just wonderful. Highly recommended.

reviews.title: Nice food
reviews.text: We had dinner here on our way to the islands. We had some nice dishes, but it took quite some time between each course. The dining room on the right side of the building has some more lively atmosphere than the one on the left, which has a more private dining sphere.

reviews.title: Food is very good and atmosphere
reviews.text: Food is very good and atmosphere exceptional.  The service was very friendly but painfully slow.  Expensive

reviews.title: Tops tops! Bravo
reviews.text: Had lunch with the family. This was fantastic. Very good food and service. Ambiance, location, design, all very good. These guys could get a star from Michelin. Well done!!

reviews.title: Lucky find
reviews.text: May 2018 we cycled through Harlingen saying it looked nice and we should returned. We returned on Sunday as part of an autumnal trip. Saw this restaurant on a walk through the town and took a chance on them having a space, we were in luck in more ways than one. Food, setting and friendliness of staff was excellent. Even a few additional course surprises which added to the evening. I had beef and my husband the lamb, both cooked to perfection and the tuna i had to start was just fabulous. Highly recommend this place and possibly booking if you don't want to be disappointed, even in the low season! Thank you :-)

reviews.title: An excellent restaurant
reviews.text:
This restaurant provided the excellent venue for a birthday celebration, and the cuisine, staff service and location could not have been better.  We were visiting Harlingen in our sailing boat, and the restaurant was only a few minutes walk from the marina, and Trip Advisor and the reviews sold the idea of the venue to us.

It was also a very friendly restaurant, both from other diners, and also from the staff, with no hurry to serve the different courses, just take it at your own speed.

reviews.title: Outstanding food and service.
reviews.text: We had an outstanding “verrassingsmenu” at this beautiful Harlingen restaurant. The flavors were unique and the dishes nicely prepared. Be sure to accompany some dishes with their nice wines! The interior was super cute, with lots of greenery, glass, and an open kitchen. The service was also tops - friendly and competent. I notified them of a severe allergy ahead of time and the kitchen thoughtfully prepared a dessert that I could enjoy. Impressive attention to the customer! Compliments to the staff. I’d happily return.

reviews.title: Excellent food for reasonable price
reviews.text: Perfect and surprising combinations of taste and ingredients. Great hospitality by Ms. Inez Poldervaart and her staff.

reviews.title: Fine dinner
reviews.text: Restaurant ‘t Havenmantsje is located in a picturesque harbour building overlooking the old harbour of Harlingen. The food is price quality wise good, but lacks refinement and some sort of balance between fresh acidity and rich more rounder flavors. Particular favorites of our dinner where the Thom kha Gai soup and the deer main course.

reviews.title: Perfect location with delicious food
reviews.text:
The Restaurant is placed in the middle of the pier. 

The location and design of the restaurant is great. 

We’ve bought the house wine and it was delicious. 

For starter you’ll get bred and greeting from the kitchen which are perfect decorated. 

We’ve got also soup in shells very nice idea. 

For the starter we’ve bought spring rolls which looks like sushi rolls also very tasty. 

The main course was beef it was so tender and tasty you’ll love it! 

There are also a lot of other tasty and out of ordinary foods on the menu and you can also choose different menus I.e 3 course menu. 

You have to visit this restaurant!

reviews.title: Don't miss this on your way to Terschelling or Vlieland !
reviews.text: 'Uitstekend', excellent is, in short, the verdict about the restaurant located in this bucolic brick building in the harbour of Harlingen in Friesland on the Dutch coast. Fine cuisine, arranged mainly around 3 - 6 course menus which feature modern and nuanced variations of meat, fish, vegetables and more, most of it regionally or locally sourced. The wine pairings are to be recommended as well. The service is very attentive and friendly. Give yourself time and enjoy !

reviews.title: A litte gem that we discovered by accident
reviews.text: Returning back from Vlieland, on of the Dutch so-called wadden islands, we were looking for a place to eat in the town of Harlingen when it started to rain. We quickly entered the restaurant 't Havemantsje and without much hope - the restaurant seemed solidly filled - we inquired for a table for two. By sheer luck there was just one small table left on the first floor. This turned out a great place to be. We had we very enjoyable evening which lasted longer that we had anticipated but with no regret. The food was very good and the service was excellent. This restaurant preformed better that many of Michelin star rated restaurants we have visited. Nice size portions and lovely amuses in between. When the check came we had another positive surprise. A place well worth the visit.

photo.caption: One of the amuses. Simple but delicate

reviews.title: Great location but ...
reviews.text: Went for lunch during the Tall Ship Race event. Since we were during a special event, I'm not sure we experienced the restaurant at its best. A BBQ had been set outside and offered burgers, kip sate or salmon for about 7 euro. A daily 2 or 3 dish menu was also on offer but we were not given access to a menu card or a drink card to check prices. Overall service was messy, even if smiley, and food (BBQ) was average at best. The space : a large veranda situated at the entrance of the harbor is really nice, so maybe worth another visit in a calmer moment.

reviews.title: Laying it on thick: eye-catching dishes
reviews.text:
My date took me out to this ‘upper class’ restaurant. We sat out in the conservatory, which looks absolutely gorgeous. Very modern and sleek.

The restaurant offers good service and high quality food. The dishes are real eye-catchers: every course looked beautiful. 
The only thing was: I didn’t enjoy the food so much. I felt like they were trying too hard. Putting so many flavours into such a tiny dish (I mean seriously, it was just one or two bites in a dish) is just too much!
There was hardly any balance between the foods and flavours and I felt that they let these beautiful products go to waste by adding so much stuff. 

Personally I just like a good plate of real food. Nothing too fancy, just good flavours and enough food on my plate. 
So this restaurant and it’s eye-catching dishes are just not my cup of tea. But if you’re really into kickshaw and you have plenty of cash (it’s an expensive restaurant - fortunately my date was really nice ;)), this could be the place for you.

reviews.title: Outstanding quality and service
reviews.text: Visiting Harlingen en route between Terschelling and Schiphol on a trip home to Hobart, Tasmania, I chanced upon this restaurant, set across from the ferry terminal in a beautiful brick and blue-tiled building at the harbour. The service was courteous and immaculately professional. A monolingual speaker (sadly) I was taken through a comprehensive and adventurous menu, settling upon a white asparagus and smoked salmon salad and grilled sea bream with smoked eel foam, accompanied by a delightful sauvignon blanc. In advance of these dishes being served, the staff also presented a miniature taco filled with spicy hummus and lightly pickled cabbage, a surprising and refreshing sorbet of purple and orange heritage carrots, and a miso soup served in a conch shell! The atmosphere was calm and welcoming, and after a week of conferencing on Terschelling, was just the ticket to wind down and reorient. I would highly recommend this restaurant to others who have the good luck to stay in this delightful harbour town.

reviews.title: Excellent in every way
reviews.text:
We walked past on a sunny day and decided to stop for lunch since the terrace looked so inviting. We were pleasantly surprised when the menu arrived, to discover that it was very different from the typical lunch menu in the Netherlands and had all sorts of interesting looking dishes. We decided to splash out and my wife had the lobster and I had the lamb prepared two ways. Since this is more than we normally eat at lunch we didn't order a first course, but the restaurant gave us not one but three amuses while we were waiting for our food. All the food was both tasty and imaginative. 

This restaurant functions as a Grand Cafe, which means that you can stop for a full meal, a snack or just a drink. It is the first Grand Cafe I have been too which serves gourmet food. 
 
Service was excellent and the location, overlooking the harbour, is great.Lunch for two including two soft drinks each  and a coffee came to just under 90 Euro, which was good values considering we ordered dishes with expensive ingredients.  I'lll definitely go back.

reviews.title: Food fabulous...service not so much
reviews.text: We were thrilled to find a Micheline restaurant in Friesland and we’re excited to have a good dinner. We sat down for 15 minutes before anyone came to our table. Because we’d read the reviews on TripAdvisor we knew there was a surprise menu and so we requested info on it. The waitress gave us a short brief and so we ordered that with the accompanying wine and no pork. The first course came with no wine and with pork! We corrected them and it was replaced. The food is fabulous so our compliments to the chef but the service was disorganized. Our sommelier, Ines was great. She was friendly and had a beautiful smile. We would definitely go back for the food but hope the service is better.

reviews.title: Mother's day lunch
reviews.text:
We ate again delicious food and enjoyed at this great location. 
Mother's day lunch was fantastic. Each component of the dishes was made to perfection. We had more sweets this time... desserts were elegant, modern and had surprising new flavour combinations.
As always, they took into account the food allergies of my son and adapted all the dishes. He loved the food. 
Thank you so much!!

reviews.title: Excellent.
reviews.text:
This really is the only place to go
In the area . 
I went twice and was exceptionally impressed .
On my second visit we arrived with a party of 15 and we were seen to without flaw . 
Both the kitchen and the front of house are amazing . 
Hospitality and execution were spot on . 
I can not recommend this place highly enough . 
They also have a cooking school upstairs .

reviews.title: Beautiful and stylish restaurant looking over the harbour
reviews.text:
This is such a beautiful place to go dine in Harlingen. I had the two course surprise menu which was absolutely delicious. a starter of perfectly seared tuna with pickled vegetables and a chive sauce, followed by beautifully cooked steak on a celeriac puree and vegetables. Prior to our meal we had a fresh amuse of diced beetroot with a beetroot sorbet - which i found lovely - and a cheese cracker. All this for only €22. Great value.

The restaurant is very stylishly decorated. some of the chairs in the conservatory part have been upholstered with colourful fabric and look great. additionally, they are extremely comfy. Overall a very pleasant find on our trip to Harlingen.

Two points for improvement however:
1. An English menu would be helpful for non Dutch speaking customers
2. When a Gin and Tonic is meant to contain raspberries, they are in there for a reason. Don't just replace with lime when you haven't got any more raspberries. The flavour of the drink will be affected.

I will definitely recommend this restaurant to friends, family and colleagues.

reviews.title: High end dining in Harlingen
reviews.text:
This restaurant aspires to be a high end restaurant and ... it generally succeeds at this very well.

The old part of the building offers very classic surroundings where you sit in soft cozy chairs at white linen decked tables. Acoustics also mean that you are not bothered at all by other tables.

In 2017 a new annex was opened that offers a more 'rowdy' environment. Ultra modern with glass, stone, and generally 'younger' styling. 

The food served in both parts is the same though. Marco Poldervaart knows how to cook and indeed how to cook very well.

The only downside is that if you return quickly then you're likely to encounter the same appetizers or the same courses in the simpler menus.

reviews.title: Fancy restaurant with  a view
reviews.text:
Excellent experience: the surprise menu.

Didn’t like the Caribbean fish: scobia

The best were the starter surprises!

reviews.title: Probably best in Town
reviews.text: This restaurant is on the best location you can imagine in Harlingen. Harlingen is a great destination on it's own, this restaurant however makes it even more attractive. We took the 'surprise menu' and it was a very pleasant surprise indeed. Great local produce, full of flavour. Everything was a real treat. Even the bathroom was perfect, with Aesop hand wash, now that's what I call a real eye for every detail.

reviews.title: Delicious!
reviews.text:
My family has been here many times before, for me this was the first time. We were sitting upstairs at a table viewing the harbor and that brought back some beautiful childhood memories. 
We had the surprise diner option of 6 courses, all served with perfect matching wines. Every single bite was amazing. 'T Havenmantsje is pure bliss to me.
The staff was very professional, experienced and had fun doing their job. I really love places like this that make you feel so welcome!
I'm sure I'll be back soon

reviews.title: Gorgeous location, beautiful restaurant
reviews.text:
The location of the restaurant is exceptional.
We sat in the serre, the new room, which has a beautiful modern/rustic decor.

The service is very good. The hostess is very professional and into the detail.

When we visited, the restaurant was almost full, but we didn't have to wait too long in between dishes. Just the normal waiting time. They served us apetizers in between, which were nice.

The restaurant has a system where you can choose 3, 4, or 5 dishes, big or small. They break the mould about "starters" and "main courses", which gives more flexibility. I personally wanted to eat two of the small dishes and one dessert. They push a little too hard on you taking more and bigger dishes. I think that three dishes and wine plus coffee with bonbons is ok, taking also into account that my husband took all biger dishes, and different types of wine.
The savory dishes were delicious (the one with scallops and cauliflower was really lovely), and were on a higher culinary level than the dessert. Dessert could be better for this restaurant's rank.

In resume, it is a great restaurant and we will be visiting again soon.

reviews.title: Lovely place to eat
reviews.text: This resturant serves amasing food well presented and served by pleasent staff, they know exatly what they are serving you and are confident in suggesting drink to acompany your meal.

reviews.title: Astoundingly good
reviews.text:
One of, if not the very best, restaurants I've been to. We were wandering through Harlingen and the new glad extension caught our eye. I thought the décor and ambience was great and we decided to stay. 3 beautifully judged little amuse bouche were brought to the table whilst waiting for our starters. I had an octopus dish, that was like a mini tide pool in appearance and was absolutely delicious. The mussel broth had been jellied into a shell shape and mixed with squid ink to resemble a mussel. This sitting in an amazingly intense and fragrant broth with seaweeds and the seafood. Quite beautiful. Our wine was a fabulous Chilian malbec. I could go on and on about the quality of the other courses, but instead, I strongly advise you to go and sample some sensational cookery. Service was impeccable and we finished chatting away to a lovely Dutch couple at the next table. Despite the Michelin stars quality of the food, there remained a lovely informality about the place. A grappa digestif and then we were presented with the bill. 
WOW. All of this did NOT come with a serious or tag and we couldn't really believe it was only £60 a head.
If fly back with a special one just to eat here. If you are anywhere near please go and treat yourself to some of the very best food anywhere.
Fabulous

reviews.title: Wonderful
reviews.text: We had the chefs 5 course surprise menu and this was a great choice. We had a table upstairs by the window and could see the lighthouse we were staying at from our table which made it extra special.

reviews.title: A culinary experience
reviews.text:
We arrived without a booking and we're pleased to still get a table as it was our anniversary. Friendly staff greeted us and settled us in with how the menu worked.
We chose a 3 course set menu which we all thoroughly enjoyed. There were also small complimentary dishes along the way and well spaced so you didn't feel overfull. 
It was a delight and the atmosphere was also lovely. 
If in this area again we would love to come back and enjoy.

reviews.title: good food, good venue, poor management
reviews.text:
Its a lovely building in a fine location.
We really enjoyed the food and could see why it was so highly rated.
However on the night we were there the service was desperately slow and the restaurant manager/maitre'd did nothing to address this.  It was almost an hour before we got our starter though we did have three - yes I think it was three - largely unmemorable "amuse bouches" in the first twenty minutes. This just seemed odd at the time. I was waiting for my starter and the glass of wine that accompanied each dish.

We waited at least an hour, possible slightly more, for our main course.  Half way through we were almost served a course we hadn't ordered and after that was whisked away, with promises of investigations etc, we heard nothing for another half hour at least.

The maitre 'd was in the restaurant but seemed to be otherwise engaged!  Difficult to avoid eye contact in a dining room that size but she succeeded.

We had a three course meal and were there for about 3 hours. They did offer a six course menu, I suspect anyone who had ordered that were still there at 1.00am

We probably hit it on a bad night - staffing shortages or some such I guess. 

I have still rated it as very good because its a lovely place to be and the food, when it arrived, was excellent. But at this level you expect the full package.  Waiters shrugging their shoulders and saying don't ask me where your meal is ( charmingly done though it was ) is not good enough.

Oh and the restaurant faces due west and had taken its blinds down for cleaning/maintenance. Doh!  Blinding your customers with the setting sun is not too clever either. It took a fellow diner to intervene and try to create some shade for a neighbouring table.

I will go there again as I am sure it could be one of the best restaurants in Harlingen.  We probably got it on a bad night - and timing courses is notoriously difficult.  An explanation would have been polite, appropriate  and well received.

reviews.title: Exquisite dining in a wonderful historic building
reviews.text: We have had the pleasure a number of times now and every time it is truly delightful cuisine and very convincing service. Surprise choice has been the best so far and the chef is really ***** star! Super and worth every buck!

reviews.title: Brilliant
reviews.text: We got a place at the chefs table completely by accident and we were bowled over by the passion and pure mastery of the chef. If you get the opportunity take it!!!

reviews.title: Wonderful food, great staff, great view
reviews.text: The best restaurant at Harlingen. Fresh, regional food at a reasonable price. Real 'dining out', with a lovely harbourview. A very obliging staff, everything is tiptop correct.

reviews.title: lunch on the boulevard in Harlingen
reviews.text: When visiting Friesland in March we went to Harlingen to visit the old town and inner and outher harbour. We had lunch in this interesting and good-looking restaurant overlooking the harbour in a nicely restored building. We were welcomed by a friendly waitress and got a nice table at the window where we could overlook the boulevard. We ordered lunch although quite some visitors were already enjoying a larger meal during lunchtime. The interior is chique and the ambiance as well. This is really a good choice if you want to spend a nice time for lunches and dinners with friends enjoying what the kitchen prepares. Their choice on the menu is large and the wine list is also impressive. They treat their customers with dignity and respect and that shows. Compliments to chef and owners of the place.

reviews.title: Outstanding. Michelin star quality
reviews.text: Haarlingen is an interesting old port and well worth a visit but it's worth going just to have dinner here. The food is absolutely outstanding and great value. We had the three course fixed price menu which offered a choice of most of the a la carte menu and every dish was of the very highest quality. But there were also three appetisers from the chef before the first course! And a sorbet after the main! So in fact seven courses. All were innovative and delicious. This would rank with the best food we have eaten anywhere in the world. Service was excellent, decor is modern in a wonderful old building and tables are well spaced. A must do experience.

reviews.title: Amazing
reviews.text: Wonderful culinary experience, great location and excellent service. Try the surprise menu and you won't be disappointed. The price is correct considering the quality of food and service. Highly recommend!

reviews.title: Don't miss this culinary gem in Harlingen. Just do it!
reviews.text: Wonderful experience. Got our timing all wrong today and arrived at the door with no reservation in shorts and cadual shorts (its worth dressing up for 't Havenmantsje...) with two (well-behaved) golden retrievers in tow. We were shown to a private dining room on the first floor (the last table in the house!) with a welcoming, "can do" smile. Two G&Ts promptly served with two bowls of water for Mini & Lola. The 6-course tasting menu  was stupendous. Its all about flavour here. Food is worth a star for sure. Great service from Lenora, Tim and sommelier Hero. We are regulars through the port of Harlingen en route to Terschelling each summer. Girst time here. Can't imagine we'd ever want to eat anywhere else in future... If in Harlingen, just do it!

reviews.title: "Verbluffingsmenu" 5 gerechten (inclusief 3 amuses) € 52,50
reviews.text: Last month we had a terrific dinner at 't Havenmantsje. We had reserved a table (recommended). The meal was a combination of different kinds of meat, veggies and other, all accompanied by a good glass of wine. The waitresses were very kind, and gave good information on all the food and wine. The location is fantastic: just near the harbour.

reviews.title: Fine cuisine, nice views
reviews.text:
Greatly enjoyed our lunch at the "Little Harbourman". Beautiful building and location. 
Restaurant has several small rooms which enhance the intimate atmosphere. See their website for a good impression.

reviews.title: Ridiculously priced
reviews.text:
....and I mean in a good way!!!
We went to 't Havenmantsje for their Sunday brunch and were pleasantly surprised. We expected for EUR 18.75 some nice eggs and rolls but we were wrong. We were served a very nice 3-course set menu plus some amuses. 
Very elegant, simple and creative cooking using fresh ingredients, a waitress who was both nice and professional, a fantastic location at the Harlingen harbour.
The duck breast we had as our main was very very well cooked and the plate looked wonderful.

reviews.title: Amazing restaurant
reviews.text: This restaurant is amazing. A beautiful dining room with a great view of the harbour with tall boats. We both ordered the Frisian mustard soup to start. This was quite simply the best soup I've ever tasted, anywhere. I then had beef croquettes which came with fresh brown bread and butter, along with more mustard. Delicious. My partner had a 'Waddenbruin' sandwich with oxtail and pickles. He thought it was very good too, balanced flavours. All this, plus friendly service, for a very reasonable 30 euros. We're going back on our way home!

reviews.title: Well deserved top rated restaurant!!!
reviews.text: We walked in on a rainy saturday night without reservation, hoping to try our luck. Of course the restaurant was full. The maitre'd gave us umbrellas and recommended another place which was started by their ec-sous chef. I thought that was such great sport and confidence for them to do so!!! We had a great evening following their recommendation and went back to return the umbrella. We met the owner and shared our regret not dining there that night. She happily offered to book us in for their brunch next morning which offer we took up. We stayed later than planned to try their brunch menu. and my god, it was worth way more than the 17eur each of us paid for a 3 course fine-dining brunch with wine we had. I had amazing scallop for starter and delicious duck with beet root sauce as main. There was proper explanation about all our dishes from the host. And as a demanding foodie, i was very pleased with the food and especially the Dutch's attempt at good service which was actually the best i've had in the country so far - out of tens and tens restaurant of all level i have been to in this country!! Plan early with reservation if possible. Otherwise the brunch is also a great next best choice! This is a place not to be missed if ur in friesland.

reviews.title: Outstanding
reviews.text: Total package - décor, service and especially the food. We enjoyed the 5 course surprise tasting menu. Each and every course had a complexity and variety of complementary flavours that left us wanting more after every course, but left us completely satisfied at the end of the experience.

reviews.title: Unexpectedly sublme
reviews.text: Went to this restaurant for a quick lunch and we were totally amazed by the quality, taste and value for money. Brilliant

reviews.title: Superb food and service with passion
reviews.text: This was definitely up there with our favourite foody memories. In particular, the delicate flavours of the lamb with a pistachio and herb crust combined with the sauce, flavoured with ras-al-hanout, were to die for. The service is among the best we have ever experienced. Nothing is too much trouble and they really care that you enjoy your meal.
